# CampusFlow AI MVP Rule

## Product Definition
- Build `CampusFlow AI`: a startup-grade campus collaboration platform with AI productivity + placement workflows.
- Prioritize a production-ready feel (clean UX, consistent patterns, scalable code organization) over hackathon-only shortcuts.

## Required Repository Structure
- Keep two top-level app folders: `frontend/` and `backend/`.
- Backend must include: `controllers/`, `routes/`, `models/`, `middleware/`, `config/`, `utils/`, `server.js`, `package.json`, `.env.example`.
- Frontend must include: `src/pages/`, `src/components/`, `src/layouts/`, `src/services/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/context/`, `src/App.jsx`, `src/main.jsx`, `package.json`, `vite.config.js`.

## Mandatory Stack and Runtime
- Frontend: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS, React Router, Axios.
- Backend: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB (Mongoose).
- AI integration: Google Gemini API via backend endpoint `POST /api/ai/generate`.
- Run frontend and backend on separate ports during development.
- Keep deployment-ready conventions for Vercel (frontend) and Railway/Render (backend).

## Roles and Access
- Implement role-based access with at least `student` and `admin`; include `recruiter` when feasible.
- Use JWT authentication (register, login, role selection, protected routes, server-side role checks).

## Phase 1 Features That Must Work
- Auth: register/login with JWT and protected routes.
- Dashboard: welcome, upcoming events, tasks, placements, AI suggestions.
- Collaboration feed: create/like/comment/delete post, categories (`Placement`, `Projects`, `Learning`, `Clubs`).
- Task management: create/update/delete/complete task.
- Placement section: list placements, apply action, resume upload support.
- Events/clubs: create event, join event, list events.
- AI assistant panel: learning roadmap, project ideas, task generation, resume feedback.

## Required Pages
- `Login`, `Register`, `Dashboard`, `Feed`, `Tasks`, `Placements`, `Events`, `Profile`.

## UI/UX Constraints
- Use a modern SaaS visual language: sidebar layout, rounded cards, soft shadows, gradient CTAs, vibrant but readable theme.
- Keep interactions simple and human-friendly; optimize clarity for student users.

## Delivery and Quality
- Favor clean architecture (separation by responsibility, reusable services/hooks/components).
- Ensure API contracts are explicit and consistent between frontend services and backend routes.
- Track implementation progress with a persistent feature task list and update it as work is completed.
